    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to a friend (Brussels, 15 December 1531)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1"> 1. They have safely returned from Tournai, where the
                            Emperor had the new members of the Order of the Golden Fleece elected.
                            When they were leaving the city, he saw that the Queen wanted to hunt,
                            so he rode ahead and did the four-day journey in one and a half days. 2.
                            Now he has some time to do something, but he is anxious, he is
                            alternating between hope and fear for the fate of his homeland. Even if
                            King Ferdinand I and King John I make peace, it will not be beneficial
                            for them, and he will be facing a very bitter fate, far from his
                            homeland and his friends. He does not know if he made the right decision
                            when he trusted the Queen to come here, and he awaits his friend’s
                            advice.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/E8FCF14A-F08B-491C-AA42-940EF7C1DFB3
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad amicum.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Felicibus avibus reversi ex <placeName>Tornaco</placeName><note
                        xml:id="note.1">Tournai, for his destination see Ep. 187, and Ep.
                            189.<ref>olahus.tei.15311123_1</ref></note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15311210_1</ref>
                    sumus, civitate non undequaque inter alias Flandriae civitates inferiore, tum
                    propter sui munitionem situsque bonitatem, tum propter arcis, quae in ea est,
                    insignem fortitudinem. Dum istic eramus, pigebat nos diu istic esse ob aëris
                    intemperiem et magnam pluviarum vim ac tempestatem. Et vix exspectabamus
                    reditum, qui ideo dilatus fuit diebus aliquot, quod <persName>caesar</persName>
                    erat occupatus in creandis novis in locum demortuorum militibus Velleris
                        Gedeonis.<note xml:id="note.2">See Ep. 187. Note
                            9.<ref>olahus.tei.15311123_1</ref></note></p>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/C87381C5-955C-4BDA-9A02-858EBB62D777
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ego dum egressi sumus urbem, <persName>reginam</persName> ad duo vel
                    tria comitatus sum equitando miliaria, postea vero cum viderem eam aucupiis et
                    aliis rebus venatoriis deditam esse,<note xml:id="note.3">On Queen Mary’s
                        passion for hunting see Ep. 67. Note 1., and <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Kerkhoff</hi> 2005, 144–146.<ref>olahus.tei.15300328_1</ref></note>
                    pertaesus tantae morae praeveni eam recta huc <placeName>Bruxellas</placeName>
                    reversus, illudque itineris, quod regina quattuor confecit diebus, uno et medio
                    transegi.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">[2.] Nunc licet in otio aliquando hic agam, tamen non parum
                    sollicitor de rebus meis Hungaricis. Interque spem et metum pendeo. Spem habeo
                    aliquam, ut aliquando pacem in <placeName>Hungaria</placeName> simus habituri.
                    Metuo autem, ne etiam pace secuta non parum incommodi nobis accidat, propterea
                    quod alienas secuti simus partes. Nam pacem aliter fieri despero, quam si cum
                        <persName>Ioanne</persName> fuerit concordatum et ei regnum
                        <placeName>Hungariae</placeName> relictum. Quod si fiet nobis, qui regem
                    hunc nostrum secuti sumus, parum commodi haec pacificatio est allatura. Me autem
                    hic in externa patria perseverare et aliorum exspectare opes, etiam favente mihi
                    regina, acerbissimum esse videtur, maxime cum amicis caream et procul a patria,
                    sanguine et necessitudine iunctos mihi videre non possim. <quote
                        xml:id="quote.1">Neque enim et ipse ferreus sum, qui non movear amicorum et
                        propinquorum necessitudine</quote>,<note type="quote" xml:id="note.quote.1"
                        >Cf. Cic. <hi rend="italic">In Cat.</hi> IV,3: “Nec tamen ego sum ille
                        ferreus, qui fratris carissimi atque amantissimi praesentis maerore non
                        movear horumque omnium lacrumis, a quibus me circumsessum videtis.”</note>
                    utrum igitur consilium mihi eligendum sit, an fortunaene exponendum, vel
                    manendum in tenui conditione, fretus promissione et benivolentia
                        <persName>reginae</persName> non satis constituere possum. Tu, qui iam ob
                    aetatem grandem multa et vidisti et fecisti et expertus es, fac me tui consilii
                    participem. Et si quid ad rem meam facere iudicaris, cures ut id sciam
                    celeriter. Scio te mei semper curam habuisse, quam maximam perficias, ut nunc
                    quoque experiar tuam mihi non defuisse operam. Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5"><placeName>Bruxellis</placeName> XV. Decembris MDXXXI.</p>
            </div>
